Kasar Sin ta sanar da cewa yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da Aids ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar a ƙasar.
An samu sabbin mutane 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na shekara ta 2018 kawai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka suna gudana ta hanyar jima'i, suna nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri ta wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon karban jini.
Amma, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke rayuwa da HIV da Aids a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru zuwa mutane 100,000.
Yada HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An haramta jima'i tsakanin maza da mata a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma an ce ana nuna wariya ga LGBT.
Bisa ga ra'ayin da ake da shi game da 'yancin kai a kasar, wani bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suka yi jima'i da maza za su auri mata a ƙarshe.
Yawancin cututtuka suna faruwa ne domin rashin kariya ta jima'i a cikin wannan dangantaka.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samun damar yin amfani da maganin HIV a duniya a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance matsalar.
