A ranar Asabar, birnin New York zai yi bikin Global Citizen Festival, wani biki na shekara-shekara da ke nuna jerin taurari da suka yi wa'azi da ban sha'awa, da kuma abin tunawa da manufa; kawar da talauci a duniya.
Yanzu, a shekara ta bakwai, bikin Global Citizen zai ga dubban mutane suna zuwa babban lambu a Central Park ba kawai don jin daɗin ayyukan Janet Jackson, Cardi B, da Shawn Mendes ba, har ma don wayar da kan jama'a game da ainihin manufar wannan taron, wato kawar da matsanancin talauci a shekarar 2030.
Bikin Global Citizen, wanda aka fara a shekarar 2012, ci gaba ne na Global Poverty Project, wata kungiya ce ta kasa da kasa da ke neman kawo karshen talauci ta hanyar kara yawan mutanen da ke fama da talauci.
Don samun tikiti kyauta don taron (sai dai idan kuna son ku biya tikitin VIP), masu halartar zauren za su yi ayyuka da yawa kamar su zama masu ba da gudummawa, aika imel zuwa shugabannin duniya, yin kira, ko wasu hanyoyi masu ma'ana don taimakawa wajen wayar da kan jama'a game da burinsu na kawo ƙarshen talauci.
Amma, yaya Global Citizen ya yi nasara a cikin shekaru 12 da suka gabata wajen cimma burinsa?
Shin ra'ayin bayar da kyauta ta kyauta a wani taro hanya ce mai kyau don sa mutane su yi wani abu, ko kuma wani abu ne da ake kira "clicktivism" - mutane suna jin kamar suna yin bambanci ta hanyar sanya hannu kan wata takarda ta yanar gizo ko kuma aikawa da tweet?
Tun daga shekarar 2011, Global Citizen ta ce ta yi rikodin fiye da miliyan 19 na "aiki" daga magoya bayanta, yana sa ta kafa wasu manufofi.
An ce wannan aikin ya taimaka wajen sa shugabannin duniya su sanar da kudade da manufofi da suka kai dala biliyan 37 da za su shafi mutane sama da biliyan 2.25 a shekarar 2030.
A farkon shekarar 2018, kungiyar ta tattara alkawuran da aka yi 390 da kuma sanarwar da suka fito daga ayyukanta, aƙalla dala biliyan 10 daga cikinsu an tura su ko kuma an yi tarin kudade.
Kungiyar ta kiyasta cewa kudaden da aka ba da su sun yi tasiri ga kusan mutane miliyan 649 a duniya.
