Majalisar White House ta ce, wataƙila za a sake jinkirta taron Trump da Rosenstein.
Babban taron Donald Trump da mataimakin babban lauya Rod Rosenstein na iya "dakatar da mako guda" saboda gwagwarmayar dan takarar shugaban kotun koli Brett Kavanaugh na ci gaba, fadar White House ta ce a ranar Lahadi.
Rosenstein yana kula da aikin mai ba da shawara na musamman Robert Mueller, wanda ke binciken tsoma baki na Rasha a cikin zaben, alaƙar da ke tsakanin masu goyon bayan Trump da Rasha, da kuma yiwuwar da shugaban ya hana adalci.
Ko Trump zai kori mataimakin babban lauya ko a'a, wanda zai yi barazana ga 'yancin Mueller, ya jawo jita-jita a Washington na tsawon watanni.
A farkon wannan watan, New York Times ta ruwaito cewa Rosenstein ya tattauna ta amfani da tarho don yin rikodin tattaunawar da ya yi da Trump da kuma yiwuwar tsige shugaban kasa ta hanyar Kwaskwarima ta 25.
Rosenstein ya musanta rahoton.
Amma a ranar Litinin da ta gabata, ya tafi fadar White House, a tsakiyar rahoton cewa zai yi murabus.
A maimakon haka, an sanar da cewa zai gana da Trump, wanda a lokacin yana ofishin Majalisar Dinkin Duniya a New York, a ranar Alhamis.
Trump ya ce zai "zaɓa kada" ya kori Rosenstein, amma an sake jinkirta taron don kauce wa rikici da kotun shari'a ta Majalisar Dattawa inda Kavanaugh da wata mace da ta zarge shi da aikata laifuka na jima'i, Dr Christine Blasey Ford, za su ba da shaida.
A ranar Juma'a, Trump ya ba da umarnin FBI ta gudanar da bincike na mako guda kan ikirarin da Kavanaugh ya yi, wanda daga bisani ya jinkirta cikakken zaben Majalisar Dattawa.
Sakataren yada labarai na Trump, Sarah Sanders, ta bayyana a gidan talabijin na Fox News Sunday.
Da aka tambaye shi game da ganawar da ya yi da Rosenstein, ya ce: "Ba a riga an yi kwanan wata ba, amma a wannan makon, zan ga cewa jinkirta zuwa mako na gaba yana da kyau idan aka yi la'akari da sauran abubuwan da suka faru a kotun koli.
